walkDir spool-storm bug + fix (gm plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js, fixed 2026-05-27): the watcher walkDir recursed unconditionally into ALL subdirs of .gm/exec-spool/in/, so a stray nested dir (e.g. C:/dev/zellous had in/prd-resolve/.gm/exec-spool/ from a misfire) made walkDir derive a bogus verb prd-resolve.gmexec-spool with tasks .supervisor/.watcher/.status/.turn-summary, dispatch-erroring on EVERY tick - an error storm flooding gm-log + inflating deviations_30m. FIX: walkDir(dir,depth) skips dot-prefixed dir segments AND caps depth at 2 (the verb tree is in/<verb>/[<sub>/]<N> - never deeper, never a dotdir); the recursive watch handler skips any filename with a dot-prefixed path segment too. LESSON: any recursive spool walk needs a dotdir-skip + depth-cap or a spool-inside-spool wedges it. To clean an active storm, rm the stray nested dir AND deploy the guarded walkDir.